flowRoot.flowPara: Happiness is the purpose of life. Despite this, only one in three Americans says they're very happy.

Several years ago in an interview with Connan O'Brien, Louis C. K. tells of flying on a newly equipped Wi-Fi airplane. He was amazed by the new technology. Until, during the flight, thw Wi-Fi went down. Immidiately, the man next to him became extremelu upset. "As though the world owes this man something he only knew existed 10 second ago".

Louis C. K. continues by describing people's absurd frustration with flying in general. People complain about it all the time "It was the worst day of my life! It took 20 minutes to board! We had to sit on the runaway for 40 minutes!"We hear complains like these all the time. As if we've forgotte how incredible it is that human can fly at all.
